    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the use of a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration and is accepted because the protocol is normatively specified for this device class and no alternative condition is clinically indicated. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for the stated intended use.",
